On all three days, the court documents say, Albury was viewing documents on his computer screen.
According to court documents, Wolfe had told FBI leak investigators that he had not been in contact with journalists.
According to court documents, the FBI got a “judicially-authorized pen register and trap and trace order” for Edwards’s personal cellphone.
Using this court order, the FBI was apparently able to gather real-time metadata from an encrypted messaging app on Edwards’s phone.
The court documents don’t name the messaging app that was used, and it’s not clear how the government obtained the metadata.